      "span_text": "The minimum required yield is the return a pension fund needs to achieve on a long-term basis in order to keep its financial balance. describe that the minimum required return net of asset management costs should at least consider guaranteed interest on pension liabilities, longevity risk, accumulation of value fluctuation reserves, and administration costs (1)."
